dataIdInfo.idPurp: The City of Conroe is located in Montgomery County, one of the fastest growing counties in Texas. Conroe population 71,879, is located approximately 40 miles north of downtown Houston. It surrounds Interstate Highway 45 (IH-45) that connects Dallas and Houston. IH-45 serves as Conroe main north to south corridor. Texas Highway 105 bi-sects the city east to west and connects the city to Lake Conroe to the west. Loop 336 serves to connect the remaining parts of the city. The city limits extend to the west side of Lake Conroe. At the close of 2016, the city limits of Conroe have a land area of approximately 71.3 square miles.
